dict..setDesc(\"A regular expression which ma: .setDesc("A regular expression which matches a character of a word. Used by during completion to find the word to the left of the cursor and used by the file scanner to find valid words.")
dict..setDesc(\"Whether the popup is automati: .setDesc("Whether the popup is automatically focused once it opens.")
dict..setDesc(\"Whether the popup opens autom: .setDesc("Whether the popup opens automatically when typing.")
dict..setDesc(\"The minimum length a word has: .setDesc("The minimum length a word has to be, to count as a valid suggestion. This value is used by the file scanner and word list provider.")
.setDesc("The minimum length a word has to be, to trigger suggestions. The LaTeX provider has its own separate setting.")
dict..setDesc(\"When enabled, the query 'Hell: .setDesc("When enabled, the query 'Hello' can suggest 'H\xE8ll\xF2', meaning diacritics will be ignored when filtering the suggestions. Only used by the file scanner and word list provider.")
dict..setDesc(\"Whether the LaTeX provider sh: .setDesc("Whether the LaTeX provider should trigger after dollar signs which are enclosed in code blocks (for example ```$\\fr```).")
.setDesc("Whether the LaTeX provider should ignore the casing of the typed text. If so, the input 'MaThbb' could suggest 'mathbb'.")
dict..setDesc(\"The minimum length a query ha: .setDesc("The minimum length a query has to be, to trigger suggestions.")
dict..setDesc(\"Whether the Front matter prov: .setDesc("Whether the Front matter provider should ignore the casing of the typed text. If so, the input 'MaThbb' could suggest 'mathbb'.")
dict..setDesc(\"Whether each completed tag sh: .setDesc("Whether each completed tag should be suffixed with a comma or a newline (when typing in a multi-line list). Allows faster insertion of multiple tags.")
dict..setDesc(\"If this setting is enabled, t: .setDesc("If this setting is enabled, the currently opened file will be scanned to find new words.")
dict..setDesc(\"A list of files which contain: .setDesc("A list of files which contain words to be used as suggestions. Each word should be on its own line.")
dict..setTooltip(\"Immediately scan all .md f: .setTooltip("Immediately scan all .md files currently in your vault.")
